Peru Stocks: Candente, Luz del Sur, Pomalca, Southern Copper

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-07-06T19:01:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/peru-stocks-candente-luz-del-sur-pomalca-southern-copper.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 2:28 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index dropped 0.1 percent to 19,347.55.
The MSCI All Peru Capped Index fell 0.5 percent to 2,482.64.  Industrial stocks and miners slumped on investor
uncertainty over the policies of President-elect Ollanta Humala,
said Javier Frisancho, a trader at Lima-based brokerage Kallpa
Securities SAB. Humala takes office July 28.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper
producer, dropped 4.9 percent to $31.20 after futures declined
in New York.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian
exploration company, fell 2.5 percent to $1.15.  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POMALCC1 PE), a unit of
Grupo Oviedo, dropped 4 percent to 48 centimos.  Maple Energy
Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas producer with operations
in Peru, fell 2.2 percent to 89 cents after crude declined in
New York. Luz del Sur (LUSURC1 PE), Peru’s largest electricity
distributor, slid 1.3 percent to 6.02 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  